text:
If you have been regularly investing in 4 to 5 good quality stocks since 5 to 7 years and yet  if you were sitting with 15% to 20% losses, then it surely would have been a major concern and sad thing, 

But in your case it's just a year of investing, and if you are seeing your portfolio in RED üçí and continue to invest wisely on Dips strategically, you will be surprised to see your portfolio with 12% to 25% profit in the years to come, so sit tight on the good quality stocks and set aside cash to invest wisely in good quality stocks when market corrects and hold them until the Bull run or any Massive run up comes, patience is the key üîê üëçüèª

Happy Investing ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ganesh Vadcar

text: Dev in place of being Sad, you should feel happy. As this is your first year of investments, you would be investing for very long period of time. Say for next ten years markets remains low and you just keep on investing in good quality companies, then post the initial years, markets recovers and at the time when you actually need to spend that money markets are at a high level for you to make maximum from your investments. The current fall is good for long term investors like you.... It's bad for people who were planning to take out funds for retirement or some other asset purchase... I hope I could demistify some basic concepts of investing for you.
